                <Pad Id="SD823YrigajOiwRyo9ZKgO" Bounds="2310,386,532,138" ShowValueBox="true" isIOBox="true" Value="The driest place on earth is the Atacama Desert in Chile. It is a plateau that occupies a 600 mile strip of the Pacific coast on the western side of Andes Mountains. It is the only true desert on Earth that receives lower moisture than all the polar deserts. It occupies an area of about 41,000 square miles and is mainly made up of sand, salt lakes, and rough terrain. The lack of precipitation in the desert is because of the two mountains (the Chilean coast range and Andes Mountains) that block the advection of moisture from the Atlantic and Pacific oceans, creating a 2-sided rain-shadow.">
                  <p:TypeAnnotation LastCategoryFullName="Primitive" LastDependency="VL.CoreLib.vl">
                    <Choice Kind="TypeFlag" Name="String" />
                  </p:TypeAnnotation>
                  <p:ValueBoxSettings>
                    <p:fontsize p:Type="Int32">9</p:fontsize>
                    <p:stringtype p:Assembly="VL.Core" p:Type="VL.Core.StringType">Comment</p:stringtype>
                  </p:ValueBoxSettings>
                </Pad>
